ENTRY            14866   20260331   20260617   20260617       1529
SUBENT        14866001   20260331   20260617   20260617       1529
BIB                 15         63
TITLE      Measurement of the 75As(n,2n) cross section at 14.1
           MeV at the National Ignition Facility
AUTHOR     (K.N.Kmak,J.D.Despotopulos,J.Jeet,T.L.Huynh)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,113,024317,2026)
           #doi:10.1103/n5h1-6j23
INSTITUTE  (1USALRL)
FACILITY   (LASER,1USALRL) The National Ignition Facility (NIF)
           at Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory (LLNL).
INC-SPECT  The total 4pi neutron yields of each shot were
           1.65*10**18 and 6.60*10**17 (February and March,
           respectively).
DETECTOR   (HPGE)
SAMPLE     Three GaAs foils were fielded on two NIF shots, on
           February 22, 2025, and March 22, 2025. Semiconductor
           grade GaAs foils were obtained from Wafer World Inc
            (99.99%). The foils were received as 2-in.-diam
           disks and were cut to 1 cm x 1 cm squares. Gold foils
            (Goodfellow, 99.9%) were used as monitor foils. All
           foils were weighed and then stacked in a target
           option activation device (TOAD), which is comprised
           of an aluminum base and cover (>99.9% purity).
METHOD     (ACTIV) The target material consisted of GaAs foils
           encapsulated in aluminum irradiation containers,
           along with Au monitor foils, and positioned in the
           NIF chamber during high neutron yield shots. Both NIF
           shots utilized in this work were part of the HYBRID-E
           campaign, which developed the first capsule design to
           reach ignition and now regularly performs NIF shots
           with total neutron yields >10**17. There were two
           positions in the NIF chamber used for these
           irradiations, one at 30 cm from the target chamber
           center (TCC) and the other at 9 cm. After
           irradiation, the sealed TOADs were counted at the NCF
           using high purity germanium (HPGe) detectors several
           times over two days. One detector was used for each
           TOAD. Count times ranged from 60 minutes to 6.5 hours
           with the goal of achieving ~1% counting statistics.
ANALYSIS   Based on the nuclear counting data from the Au
           isotopes and the calculated cross section for the
           197Au(n, 2n) reaction, the spectrum averaged 75As(n,
           2n) cross section can be calculated by a ratio method
           as A74/A196 = (A75*Int Phi(E)*sigma75(E) dE)/
            (A197*Int Phi(E)sigma197(E)dE),
           sigma75 = (A197*sigma197/A196)*(A74/A75), where Am is
           the atom (A) of an isotope with mass number m, Phi is
           the time-integrated neutron flux (neutron cm**-2),
           and sigma is the cross section (cm2).
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Experimental uncertainty arises largely from
           counting statistics.
           (ERR-S,,1.) The goal of achieving ~1% counting
           statistics.
           (ERR-1) The absolute calibration of the HPGe
           detectors (3%).
           (ERR-2) The masses of the foils (2%).
MONITOR    (79-AU-197(N,2N)79-AU-196,,SIG)
